10/02/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A crowd of 10,000 people gathered in downtown Sarajevo on Saturday (February 9th) to protest growing juvenile delinquency in the past few months. 
In the latest case, a 17-year-old boy was attacked by three men aboard a Sarajevo tram. 
He died of his injuries on the way to hospital. 
Three weeks ago, three teenagers of Roma origin attacked a 72-year-old woman in front of her house, spilled oil over her body and set her on fire. 
A 21-year-old man died on Friday after a fight in a Sarajevo disco. 
(Tanjug, B92, RTRS, SRNA, DPA - 09/02/08)
